						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Sundarakuchāmbāḷ shrine, Vīḻināthaśvami temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 15: 986 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records a gift of 96 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruttāṉtōṉṟi-Bhaṭṭārar at Tirumaḻalai in Veṇṇāḍu by Muṭṭan Ēḍuḍaiyār for the merit of his wife Āchchaṉ Kaliyuga-ttaṉiyuga-ttāyār Vīranāraṇiyār. The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of the place and the <hi rend="italic">panmāhēśvarar</hi> undertook to protect the gift.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 367.</p>						

						</summary>
